Brazilian Stock Movers: Braskem, BR Malls, CPFL and Petrobras

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-05-12T20:35:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/brazilian-stock-movers-braskem-br-malls-cpfl-petrobras.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index advanced 0.4 percent to 64,003.16.  Braskem SA (BRKM5)  (BRKM5 BS) climbed 4 percent to 22.75 reais.
 Latin America ’s largest petrochemicals producer said in a
regulatory filing that first-quarter net income rose to 305
million reais ($187.6 million) from 23 million reais a year
earlier.  BR Malls Participacoes SA (BRML3)  (BRML3 BS) increased 2.6 percent
to 18.10 reais. New shares of  Brazil ’s biggest owner of shopping
malls started trading in Sao Paulo today after a stock offering
by the company this week.  CPFL Energia SA (CPFE3)  (CPFE3 BS) climbed 1.4 percent to 47.55
reais. Brazil’s largest private-sector power distributor
reported first-quarter net profit of 466 million reais,
according to a regulatory filing. The average estimate of six
analysts in a Bloomberg survey was for a profit, excluding some
items, of 426.6 million reais.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  (PETR4 BS) declined 0.7 percent to
23.68 reais. Brazil’s state-controlled oil company said its
gasoline station chain BR Distribuidora will cut gasoline and
ethanol prices by 6 percent and 13 percent, respectively.  Vivo Participacoes SA (VIVO4)  (VIVO4 BS) gained 2.6 percent to
65.95 reais. Brazil’s biggest wireless carrier said in a filing
that consolidated first-quarter net income more than tripled
from a year earlier to 710.2 million reais.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in Sao Paulo at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
